00:35:06.329 --> 00:35:08.639
Any questions about this one?
 

00:35:08.639 --> 00:35:11.480
So we get equilibrium leverage
and leverage has a tremendous

00:35:11.480 --> 00:35:12.539
effect on the price.
 

00:35:12.539 --> 00:35:15.952
Why does it affect the price,
because the fact that these

00:35:15.952 --> 00:35:19.791
guys were able to borrow so much
money is what made the price so

00:35:19.791 --> 00:35:20.340
high.
 

00:35:20.340 --> 00:35:24.619
If they couldn't borrow that
would wipe out this .2.

00:35:24.619 --> 00:35:27.331
They couldn't have borrowed
that, so they would have only

00:35:27.331 --> 00:35:29.898
had this much to spend,
so the price would have had to

00:35:29.898 --> 00:35:30.768
be much lower.
 

00:35:30.768 --> 00:35:32.909
And of course these guys
wouldn't have been able to

00:35:32.909 --> 00:35:33.809
afford all of this.
 

00:35:33.809 --> 00:35:36.735
So as the price gets much lower
more people would want to buy

00:35:36.735 --> 00:35:39.027
and you would have the marginal
buyer down here,

00:35:39.027 --> 00:35:40.880
and there'd be a much lower
price.

00:35:40.880 --> 00:35:43.440
So this borrowing is what
jacked up the price.

00:35:43.440 --> 00:35:45.409
Leverage means high prices.
 

00:35:45.409 --> 00:35:48.889
It seems like the most obvious
