00:37:08.518 --> 00:37:10.849
You have to go down twice to
get .2.

00:37:10.849 --> 00:37:13.349
Otherwise Y pays off 1.
 

00:37:13.349 --> 00:37:16.443
And everyone's going to begin
at the beginning there with 1

00:37:16.443 --> 00:37:18.949
unit of Y and 1 unit of gold
just as before,

00:37:18.949 --> 00:37:23.429
and they could consume in the
middle,

00:37:23.429 --> 00:37:25.202
or they could consume in the
end, but they have no more

00:37:25.202 --> 00:37:25.630
endowments.
 

00:37:25.630 --> 00:37:27.603
All their endowments are right
at the beginning,

00:37:27.603 --> 00:37:28.989
1 unit of Y and 1 unit of gold.
 

00:37:28.989 --> 00:37:29.980
There's no discounting.
 

00:37:29.980 --> 00:37:33.550
They just care about the
expected consumption.

00:37:33.550 --> 00:37:36.909
The difference is now it takes
two periods to see the

00:37:36.909 --> 00:37:39.559
realization, so two pieces of
bad news.

00:37:39.559 --> 00:37:43.039
Now, why is that interesting,
two pieces of bad news?

00:37:43.039 --> 00:37:46.400
Well, when I was in the crisis
both in '98 when I thought about

00:37:46.400 --> 00:37:48.373
this model,
created this model,

00:37:48.373 --> 00:37:51.682
